  volume={},
  number={},
  pages={1131-1136},
  abstract={Computational Thinking is a competence that is developed more in the last few years. This is due to the multitude of benefits it has in the classroom. Throughout this article we show a series of activities that promote the development of Computational Thinking using tools that allow visual block programming. The particularity of these activities is that some of them were performed during the confinement due to the COVID-19 and other activities were performed later, in the period known as the new normality. Throughout the article, details are provided about the different sessions. The different visual programming tools by blocks and the educational scenarios used are also indicated. In addition, the results obtained are shown.},
  keywords={COVID-19;Resistors;Visualization;Remote laboratories;Tools;Light emitting diodes;Liquid crystal displays;Computational Thinking;Educational Robotics;Learning technology;STEAM},
  doi={10.1109/EDUCON46332.2021.9453903},
